xQTLbiolinks 0.1.0
  • Reference

    xQTLdownload_eqtl

    xQTLdownload_eqtl.Rd

    download significant or unsignificant eQTL data of a tissue or across all tissues. can be quried with a gene/variant-gene pair.

    Usage

    xQTLdownload_eqtl(
  variantName = "",
  gene = "",
  variantType = "auto",
  geneType = "auto",
  tissueSiteDetail = "",
  datasetId = "gtex_v8",
  recordPerChunk = 100
)

    Arguments

    variantName

    A character string. like dbsnp ID or variant id in GTEx.

    gene

    A gene symbol or a gencode id (versioned). Can not be null.

    variantType

    A character string. "auto", "snpId" or "variantId". Default: "auto".

    geneType

    A character string. "auto","geneSymbol" or "gencodeId". Default: "auto".

    tissueSiteDetail

    A character string. tissue detail can be listed using \"tissueSiteDetailGTExv8\" or \"tissueSiteDetailGTExv7\"

    datasetId

    A character string. "gtex_v8" or "gtex_v7". Default: "gtex_v8".

    recordPerChunk

    A integer value (1-500). number of records fetched per request (default: 100).

    Value

    A data.table

    Examples
